### 🔑 Key Idiomatic Rust Choices

| Python Concept | Rust Equivalent | Why It's Idiomatic |
|----------------|----------------|-------------------|
| `Optional[datetime]` | `Option<DateTime<Utc>>` | `chrono::Utc` prevents timezone bugs. `Option` replaces `None` safely. |
| `List[str]` | `Vec<String>` | Owned, contiguous memory. Rust doesn't have default args, so callers pass `vec![]`. |
| `def method(self)` | `&mut self` / `&self` | Explicit borrow checker guarantees no data races. Mutators require `&mut`, readers use `&`. |
| `return bool` for failure | `Result<(), TaskError>` | Rust prefers `Result` for fallible operations. It forces callers to handle the error explicitly. |
| List comprehension | `.iter().filter().collect()` | Zero-allocation iterator chain. Returns `Vec<&Task>` to avoid cloning. |
| `datetime.now()` | `Utc::now()` | Timezone-naive datetimes are discouraged in production. `Utc` is consistent and comparable. |
| Implicit validation | `title.trim().is_empty()` check | Fails fast with a descriptive `TaskError` instead of silently storing bad data. |

